   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>News Roundup:</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>Nothing to be Afraid of</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Csenicier</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">04/17/2002 05:23 PM CDT &nbsp;&nbsp; 2 Comments</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText"><BIG>Scheduled Sleep Time</BIG><p>Those of you who only logout to sleep on patch days will be able to get some shut-eye next week.<p><B><br>On Monday, April 22nd, at 3AM PDT, (10AM GMT), the Torvonnilous and Xegony servers will be brought down for scheduled maintenance. The estimated downtime is 8 hours.<br>On Tuesday, April 23rd, at 3AM PDT, (10AM GMT), the Tunare and Rodcet Nife servers will be brought down for scheduled maintenance. The estimated downtime is 8 hours.<p>On Wednesday, April 24th, at 3AM PDT, (10AM GMT), all servers will be brought down for a scheduled patch. The estimated downtime is 4 hours. In addition, the Quellious and Saryrn servers will have their downtimes extended for an additional 4 hours for scheduled maintenance.<p>On Thursday, April 25th, at 3AM PDT, (10AM GMT), the Mithaniel Marr and Cazic Thule servers will be brought down for scheduled maintenance. The estimated downtime is 8 hours.<p>On Friday, April 26th, at 3AM PDT, (10AM GMT), the Seventh Hammer and Morell Thule servers will be brought down for scheduled maintenance. The estimated downtime is 8 hours<br></B><p>All servers will be down on Wednesday. Hopefully the CH bug and a few others will go away afterwards.<p><BIG>Putting Your Pet on Time-out</BIG><p><B><I>As of the 4/9 patch, the casting time of the level 49 shaman pet is 16 seconds, with a 32 second cast recovery time. During the 32 seconds of recover, NO SPELLS can be cast, which is a significant change from pre-4/9.<p>Is this intentional? Did I miss the announcement?</I><p>Nope, you didn't miss an announcement. It's a bug with some pets. We'll get it fixed as soon as we can.</B><p>It's unclear if this bug only effects Shaman pets.  I would assume so, since <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral">Magicians</a> and <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum.asp?FORUM_ID=2">Necros</a> seem silent on the issue.  The Shamans do have <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?s=60d8b5ce37f9f47e69721b3b272226c0&amp;threadid=843">some</a> <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?s=60d8b5ce37f9f47e69721b3b272226c0&amp;threadid=601">reaction</a>.  But it's not your typical Verant-hates-us irate banter.  I suppose because Shaman's aren't terribly reliant on pets.<p><BIG>Enter Datharius</BIG><p><B>Hello everyone, I am the new Lead tester for Everquest, wanted to introduce myself and say a couple words about <a href = "http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000094.html">this board</a>.<br>I am sure many of you are aware that there has not been much recent activity on this forum. I just wanted to assure everyone that all of your comments that get sent to us via this forum are looked at every single day, and make up a good portion of the issues that we report.<br>You are making a difference!<br>Going forward I expect to be able to update this forum several times a week, with information on what sort of specific issues we may need help looking into, as well as informing you of issues that we are very aware of.<br>Keep the excellent comments coming in, see you in Norrath!<p>Datharius<br></B><p>Most of you remember Ester the Tester, who kept the testing board relatively busy.  Then there was some other guy for about 5 minutes that we've all forgotten about.  Now there's Datharius, who brings with him the promise of making it worthwhile to check the QA board once again.  Keep us in the loop Datharius and good luck to you.<p>For whatever reason Moorgard wasn't offered the QA Lead Tester position.  So he'll just have to keep waiting for his lucrative job offer.</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
